The paper deals with the density of graphs and their planar embeddings, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) category. Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which are also relevant to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The study of planar graphs and their properties is also related to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for characterizing optimal graphs, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
